{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_Q1yyuyFOx5gYm8Ii23nbrrdC","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Dinoki.ai app download desktop\"\n\nSearch results for query:\n\nNo links found.\n\nI'll perform a web search for information about downloading the Dinoki.ai desktop app.​```tool_call\n{\"tool_type\": \"web_search\", \"tool_input\": {\"query\": \"Dinoki.ai app download desktop\"}}\n```​Based on the search results, here's what I found about **Dinoki.ai desktop app downloads**:\n\n## Dinoki.ai Download Options\n\n**Official Website:**\n- Visit **dinoki.com** (the main domain for Dinoki/Dinoki.ai)\n- The platform appears to offer an AI-powered business/operations platform\n\n**Download Availability:**\n- Dinoki provides a **desktop application** available for download\n- The app is typically available for **Windows and macOS**\n- You may need to create an account or sign in to access the desktop download links\n\n**How to Download:**\n1. Go to the official Dinoki website\n2. Look for a \"Download\" or \"Get the App\" section\n3. Select your operating system (Windows/Mac)\n4. Alternatively, check if you're currently logged into a Dinoki workspace — there may be a direct download option in your account dashboard or settings\n\n**Note:** Since Dinoki appears to be a business/workflow platform, some downloads may be gated behind a login or admin approval if you're part of an organization.\n\nWould you like me to search for more specific information, such as direct download links, system requirements, or whether Dinoki offers a web version that doesn't require installation?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86674783-7214-4236-b263-658ed93960b9","uuid":"b1e868f4-2f5b-4b52-82e6-0d858d14b824","timestamp":"2026-05-20T09:31:11.082Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"Dinoki.ai app download desktop","results":["Search results for query:",{"content":[]},"I'll perform a web search for information about downloading the Dinoki.ai desktop app.​```tool_call\n{\"tool_type\": \"web_search\", \"tool_input\": {\"query\": \"Dinoki.ai app download desktop\"}}\n```​Based on the search results, here's what I found about **Dinoki.ai desktop app downloads**:\n\n## Dinoki.ai Download Options\n\n**Official Website:**\n- Visit **dinoki.com** (the main domain for Dinoki/Dinoki.ai)\n- The platform appears to offer an AI-powered business/operations platform\n\n**Download Availability:**\n- Dinoki provides a **desktop application** available for download\n- The app is typically available for **Windows and macOS**\n- You may need to create an account or sign in to access the desktop download links\n\n**How to Download:**\n1. Go to the official Dinoki website\n2. Look for a \"Download\" or \"Get the App\" section\n3. Select your operating system (Windows/Mac)\n4. Alternatively, check if you're currently logged into a Dinoki workspace — there may be a direct download option in your account dashboard or settings\n\n**Note:** Since Dinoki appears to be a business/workflow platform, some downloads may be gated behind a login or admin approval if you're part of an organization.\n\nWould you like me to search for more specific information, such as direct download links, system requirements, or whether Dinoki offers a web version that doesn't require installation?"],"durationSeconds":17.591337375000002,"searchCount":1}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_dJvdoEwpNWZOipzLCf3BbnFI","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Dinoki AI product what is it features\"\n\nSearch results for query: Dinoki AI product features Dinoki AI capabilities 2026 Dinoki AI product description\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Dinoki Labs\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/dinoki-ai\"},{\"title\":\"Features | Dinoki Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://docs.dinoki.ai/features\"},{\"title\":\"dinoki-ai/tweaks: AI-powered text enhancement for macOS\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/dinoki-ai/tweaks\"},{\"title\":\"Building Dinoki: Native AI companion for Mac/Windows\",\"url\":\"https://www.indiehackers.com/post/building-dinoki-native-ai-companion-for-mac-windows-4228efd94a\"},{\"title\":\"Osaurus – Complete Guide to the Native AI Edge Runtime for macOS\",\"url\":\"https://addrom.com/osaurus-complete-guide-to-the-native-ai-edge-runtime-for-macos/\"},{\"title\":\"Dinoki Pro - Unlock Premium AI Features\",\"url\":\"https://dinoki.ai/pro\"},{\"title\":\"Building on the Edge: Why We're Betting on Local-First AI\",\"url\":\"https://osaurus.ai/blog/building-on-the-edge-why-were-betting-on-local-first-ai\"},{\"title\":\"Dinoki – Privacy-First Desktop AI with Pixel Pets (6MB Native)\",\"url\":\"https://hn.algolia.com/?query=How%20we%20use%20Slack%20in%20our%20family&type=story&dateRange=all&sort=byDate&storyText=false&prefix&page=0\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what **Dinoki** is and its key features:\n\n## What is Dinoki?\n\n**Dinoki** is a **native desktop AI companion app** for **macOS and Windows** designed as a privacy-first, pixel-art AI sidekick that lives on your desktop (think Tamagotchi meets modern AI). It is built by Dinoki Labs as a fully native application—**not** an Electron web wrapper—with a focus on local processing, minimal resource usage, and data privacy.\n\n---\n\n## Key Features\n\n### 🚀 Native Performance\n- **Extremely lightweight:** ~6MB on macOS (SwiftUI) and ~69MB on Windows (WPF)\n- **Fast startup:** Launches in under 1 second\n- **Low resource usage:** Uses ~100MB RAM vs. 500MB+ for typical Electron AI apps\n- **Native OS integration:** Menu bar (Mac) / System tray (Windows), notifications, and proper OS behaviors\n\n### 💬 Smart Chat Mode (Free)\n- **Persistent memory:** Conversations continue across sessions\n- **Multiple AI providers:** Connect to Ollama, OpenAI, Anthropic, OpenRouter (300+ models), or custom providers\n- **Fully offline support:** Works without internet using the local **Osaurus** runtime\n- **Streaming responses:** Fast, real-time text feedback\n\n### 🦕 Desktop Characters / \"Pixel Pets\"\n- **Dinoki** (dinosaur): Included free, walks/jumps on your desktop, shows emotions, dances, and talks via speech bubbles\n- **Pro characters:** TomatoBoy 🍅, PigPig 🐷, and Fuegato 🐱\n- Physics-based movement and interactive animations\n\n### 🤖 Agent Mode (Pro)\n- Autonomous background task execution\n- Set goals and let Dinoki work toward them independently\n- Smart tool selection and progress updates\n- Continues working while minimized\n\n### 🛠️ Premium Tools (Pro)\n| Category | Capabilities |\n|----------|--------------|\n| **Web & Research** | Smart search, web browsing, deep research, content extraction |\n| **Productivity** | System reminders, file saving, screenshots, notes |\n| **Communication** | Slack integration, Gmail management, auto-replies |\n| **Market Data** | Weather, stock prices, crypto tracking |\n| **Automation** | Browser automation (Safari/Chrome), local app control, file system access |\n\n### 🔒 Privacy-First Design\n- **No Dinoki backend:** Connects directly to your chosen AI provider\n- **Fully local option:** Run AI offline with Osaurus (no internet needed)\n- **No data collection or analytics**\n- **Transparent permissions:** Can't see your screen or files unless explicitly shared\n\n### 🔌 MCP & Extensibility\n- **MCP (Model Context Protocol) support:** Connect Dinoki with other AI tools like Claude Desktop, Cursor, etc.\n- Add custom tool providers and integrations\n\n---\n\n## Free vs. Pro Comparison\n\n| Feature | Free | Pro |\n|---------|------|-----|\n| Chat Mode & Memory | ✅ | ✅ |\n| Multiple AI Providers | ✅ | ✅ |\n| Offline AI (Osaurus) | ✅ | ✅ |\n| Dinoki Character | ✅ | ✅ |\n| **Agent Mode** | ❌ | ✅ |\n| **All 4 Characters** | ❌ | ✅ |\n| **Web/Productivity/Comm Tools** | ❌ | ✅ |\n| **Multiple Instances** | ❌ | ✅ |\n| **Priority Support** | ❌ | ✅ |\n\n**Pricing:** Pro is a **one-time purchase** (no subscription) with lifetime updates and includes a 7-day free trial.\n\n---\n\n## Related: Osaurus\n\nDinoki can be paired with **Osaurus**, Dinoki Labs' open-source local AI edge runtime for macOS (Apple Silicon). It enables fully private, on-device inference using Apple's MLX framework and serves as the \"foundation\" that lets Dinoki run locally without sending data to the cloud.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86674783-7214-4236-b263-658ed93960b9","uuid":"3e24193d-778f-4ac5-8532-2916c5a1fa62","timestamp":"2026-05-20T09:32:18.012Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"Dinoki AI product what is it features","results":["Search results for query: Dinoki AI product features Dinoki AI capabilities 2026 Dinoki AI product description",{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_d86nuk9jj5k0u6v0raa0","content":[{"title":"Dinoki Labs","url":"https://github.com/dinoki-ai"},{"title":"Features | Dinoki Documentation","url":"https://docs.dinoki.ai/features"},{"title":"dinoki-ai/tweaks: AI-powered text enhancement for macOS","url":"https://github.com/dinoki-ai/tweaks"},{"title":"Building Dinoki: Native AI companion for Mac/Windows","url":"https://www.indiehackers.com/post/building-dinoki-native-ai-companion-for-mac-windows-4228efd94a"},{"title":"Osaurus – Complete Guide to the Native AI Edge Runtime for macOS","url":"https://addrom.com/osaurus-complete-guide-to-the-native-ai-edge-runtime-for-macos/"},{"title":"Dinoki Pro - Unlock Premium AI Features","url":"https://dinoki.ai/pro"},{"title":"Building on the Edge: Why We're Betting on Local-First AI","url":"https://osaurus.ai/blog/building-on-the-edge-why-were-betting-on-local-first-ai"},{"title":"Dinoki – Privacy-First Desktop AI with Pixel Pets (6MB Native)","url":"https://hn.algolia.com/?query=How%20we%20use%20Slack%20in%20our%20family&type=story&dateRange=all&sort=byDate&storyText=false&prefix&page=0"}]},"Based on the search results, here's what **Dinoki** is and its key features:\n\n## What is Dinoki?\n\n**Dinoki** is a **native desktop AI companion app** for **macOS and Windows** designed as a privacy-first, pixel-art AI sidekick that lives on your desktop (think Tamagotchi meets modern AI). It is built by Dinoki Labs as a fully native application—**not** an Electron web wrapper—with a focus on local processing, minimal resource usage, and data privacy.\n\n---\n\n## Key Features\n\n### 🚀 Native Performance\n- **Extremely lightweight:** ~6MB on macOS (SwiftUI) and ~69MB on Windows (WPF)\n- **Fast startup:** Launches in under 1 second\n- **Low resource usage:** Uses ~100MB RAM vs. 500MB+ for typical Electron AI apps\n- **Native OS integration:** Menu bar (Mac) / System tray (Windows), notifications, and proper OS behaviors\n\n### 💬 Smart Chat Mode (Free)\n- **Persistent memory:** Conversations continue across sessions\n- **Multiple AI providers:** Connect to Ollama, OpenAI, Anthropic, OpenRouter (300+ models), or custom providers\n- **Fully offline support:** Works without internet using the local **Osaurus** runtime\n- **Streaming responses:** Fast, real-time text feedback\n\n### 🦕 Desktop Characters / \"Pixel Pets\"\n- **Dinoki** (dinosaur): Included free, walks/jumps on your desktop, shows emotions, dances, and talks via speech bubbles\n- **Pro characters:** TomatoBoy 🍅, PigPig 🐷, and Fuegato 🐱\n- Physics-based movement and interactive animations\n\n### 🤖 Agent Mode (Pro)\n- Autonomous background task execution\n- Set goals and let Dinoki work toward them independently\n- Smart tool selection and progress updates\n- Continues working while minimized\n\n### 🛠️ Premium Tools (Pro)\n| Category | Capabilities |\n|----------|--------------|\n| **Web & Research** | Smart search, web browsing, deep research, content extraction |\n| **Productivity** | System reminders, file saving, screenshots, notes |\n| **Communication** | Slack integration, Gmail management, auto-replies |\n| **Market Data** | Weather, stock prices, crypto tracking |\n| **Automation** | Browser automation (Safari/Chrome), local app control, file system access |\n\n### 🔒 Privacy-First Design\n- **No Dinoki backend:** Connects directly to your chosen AI provider\n- **Fully local option:** Run AI offline with Osaurus (no internet needed)\n- **No data collection or analytics**\n- **Transparent permissions:** Can't see your screen or files unless explicitly shared\n\n### 🔌 MCP & Extensibility\n- **MCP (Model Context Protocol) support:** Connect Dinoki with other AI tools like Claude Desktop, Cursor, etc.\n- Add custom tool providers and integrations\n\n---\n\n## Free vs. Pro Comparison\n\n| Feature | Free | Pro |\n|---------|------|-----|\n| Chat Mode & Memory | ✅ | ✅ |\n| Multiple AI Providers | ✅ | ✅ |\n| Offline AI (Osaurus) | ✅ | ✅ |\n| Dinoki Character | ✅ | ✅ |\n| **Agent Mode** | ❌ | ✅ |\n| **All 4 Characters** | ❌ | ✅ |\n| **Web/Productivity/Comm Tools** | ❌ | ✅ |\n| **Multiple Instances** | ❌ | ✅ |\n| **Priority Support** | ❌ | ✅ |\n\n**Pricing:** Pro is a **one-time purchase** (no subscription) with lifetime updates and includes a 7-day free trial.\n\n---\n\n## Related: Osaurus\n\nDinoki can be paired with **Osaurus**, Dinoki Labs' open-source local AI edge runtime for macOS (Apple Silicon). It enables fully private, on-device inference using Apple's MLX framework and serves as the \"foundation\" that lets Dinoki run locally without sending data to the cloud."],"durationSeconds":84.54538112500002,"searchCount":1}}
