{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_78mDio4BAGkn99wpfguv1XRb","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Dinoki AI desktop companion screenshots interface UI pixel pet\"\n\nSearch results for query: Dinoki AI desktop companion screenshots Dinoki AI desktop interface UI design Dinoki AI desktop companion pixel art\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Building Dinoki: Native AI companion for Mac/Windows\",\"url\":\"https://www.indiehackers.com/post/building-dinoki-native-ai-companion-for-mac-windows-4228efd94a\"},{\"title\":\"Features | Dinoki Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://docs.dinoki.ai/features\"},{\"title\":\"Dinoki Alternatives: Top 24 Desktop Mascots & Similar Apps\",\"url\":\"https://alternativeto.net/software/dinoki/\"},{\"title\":\"Dinoki: A 5MB AI Companion That Lives on Your Mac Desktop — No Servers, No Tracking\",\"url\":\"https://alternativeto.net/software/dinoki/about/\"}]\n\nHere are the search results for **Dinoki AI** and its desktop companion interface:\n\n## What is Dinoki?\nDinoki is a **native, pixel-art AI desktop companion** (described as \"Tamagotchi vibes + GPT smarts\") that lives directly on your screen. It is designed to be extremely lightweight—**only ~6MB on Mac** (built with SwiftUI) and ~69MB on Windows (WPF)—with **no Electron** framework.\n\n## UI & Interface Details (Pixel Pet Style)\nBased on the documentation and product descriptions, the interface features:\n\n- **Pixel-Art Characters**: Animated companions that roam your desktop\n  - **Dinoki** 🦕 (the default dinosaur, free)\n  - **TomatoBoy** 🍅 (Pro)\n  - **PigPig** 🐷 (Pro)\n  - **Fuegato** 🐱 (Pro)\n\n- **Desktop Pet Behaviors**:\n  - Walks and jumps naturally around your screen\n  - Shows emotions (happy, sad, angry expressions)\n  - Dances and plays with fun animations\n  - Talks to you via **speech bubbles** with personality\n  - Follows physics with realistic movement and gravity\n\n- **Chat Interface**: A hotkey-activated chat mode for instant AI conversation\n- **Agent Mode**: Background task runner that works autonomously with progress updates\n- **Character Mode (Pro)**: The pet develops a personality and acts autonomously over time\n\n## Key UI/UX Traits\n| Feature | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| **Style** | Retro pixel art / native desktop mascot |\n| **Interaction** | Speech bubbles, hotkey chat, on-screen roaming |\n| **Privacy** | No backend; runs local/Ollama/OpenRouter. No screen/file access unless explicitly shared |\n| **Physics** | Realistic gravity and movement on desktop |\n| **Offline** | Works fully offline with local models (Ollama) |\n\n## Note on Screenshots\nWhile the search results confirm Dinoki uses a **pixel-art, Tamagotchi-style interface** with the elements described above, I cannot directly render or display image screenshots. You can view official UI screenshots and download the app at:\n- **Website**: https://dinoki.ai\n- **Docs**: https://docs.dinoki.ai\n- **Discord**: https://discord.gg/dinoki\n\nWould you like me to search for video demos, specific interface comparisons, or similar pixel-art desktop pet alternatives?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"86674783-7214-4236-b263-658ed93960b9","uuid":"0283815b-588b-45d8-b1ea-05e87a78beb9","timestamp":"2026-05-20T09:35:49.293Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"Dinoki AI desktop companion screenshots interface UI pixel pet","results":["Search results for query: Dinoki AI desktop companion screenshots Dinoki AI desktop interface UI design Dinoki AI desktop companion pixel art",{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_d86o0i2q8ins73e0ocf0","content":[{"title":"Building Dinoki: Native AI companion for Mac/Windows","url":"https://www.indiehackers.com/post/building-dinoki-native-ai-companion-for-mac-windows-4228efd94a"},{"title":"Features | Dinoki Documentation","url":"https://docs.dinoki.ai/features"},{"title":"