es aware).\n- **Privacy-First**: No backend server; connects directly to providers like OpenRouter, Anthropic, OpenAI, or local models via **Ollama/Osaurus**. It can work fully offline.\n- **Modes**: Chat Mode (free), Agent Mode for background tasks (Pro), and Character Mode where the dinosaur evolves autonomously (Pro).\n- **No Telemetry**: Claims no data collection, usage tracking, or screen/file access unless explicitly shared.\n\n## Sources\n- **Official Docs**: [docs.dinoki.ai](https://docs.dinoki.ai/) — confirms 6MB, SwiftUI, and native performance metrics.\n- **IndieHackers Post**: [Building Dinoki](https://www.indiehackers.com/post/building-dinoki-native-ai-companion-for-mac-windows-4228efd94a) — states \"6MB on Mac (SwiftUI), 69MB on Windows (WPF). No Electron.\"\n- **AlternativeTo**: [Dinoki listing](https://alternativeto.net/software/dinoki/about/) — describes it as \"under 5MB, SwiftUI-built.\"\n- **Mac Download Sites**: Chinese Mac app sites also cite \"less than 6MB\" and \"pixel wind\" (pixel art style) for the dinosaur."],"durationSeconds":59.87363087500003,"searchCount":1}}
